abstract: >-
  `pySSMF` is a Python package for running simulations with the Slave-Spin Mean-Field (SSMF) method.
  It provides a user-friendly interface to set up and solve SSMF problems, making it easier for researchers 
  to quickly run SSMF calculations for strongly correlated electron systems.